                <summary>The Republican Party of Virginia held their state convention in Richmond. A
                    delegation from Augusta attended and denounced the current state legislature as
                    illegal and disloyal. They asked Congress to order a new vote on the
                    constitution and warned the legislature against passing educational and property
                    qualifications that would keep blacks from voting.</summary>
